co2api

Class Session<T extends ContractModel>

  • java.lang.Object
    • co2api.Session<T>

  • public class Session<T extends ContractModel>
extends java.lang.Object
    A session describes a contract a contract published and merged. It is composed by a contract (belonging to a specific contract model) and a valid connection to the middleware. In a session for example you can send and receive actions or check for culpability.
    Version:
    1.3.0
    Author:
    Sebastian Podda, Livio Pompianu

      • receive

        public Message receive()
                throws ContractException
        Allows to receive the value sended by the other participant, when it was performing its action. Returns a Message element, that is an array containing two elements: the first is the name of the action performed by the counterparty, the second is the associated value (can be null). Note that the value can actually be an Integer or a String, but in both case it will be returned as string (the user must properly manage the input).
        Returns:
        A Message element: an array of strings of two elements: the name of the action performed by the counterparty and the associated value. Returns null if the counterparty hasn't performed any new action. Second element can be null if using an empty context.
        Throws:
        ContractException - In case of errors, for more informations check the exception message

      • waitUntilOnDuty

        Parameters:
